        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:43PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Alliance, or 11 miles southeast of Ravenna, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Salem, Boardman, Alliance, Canfield, Sebring, Atwater, Ellsworth,
Beloit, Deerfield, Limaville, Berlin Center, Maple Ridge, and
Greenford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
